race.comment: MAWJOOD (14) looks primed to bounce straight back. Was dominant at Rosehill two runs ago and had genuine excuses when well fancied at Coonamble last time. On the quick turnaround and dropping sharply in weight, he maps nicely and get every chance to atone. Expecting a strong rebound. DUCASSE (4) has been solid in both runs this prep, closing off well each time and now finds his pet track and trip. Kept fresh with a five-week gap and drawn ideally to stalk the speed. Looks a clear danger. VIVY AIR (6) returned with a bold effort in the G3 Cameron and will only be fitter for it. Boasts a good record here and gets a positive rider change with Brown aboard. Expect a late surge. SWIFTFALCON (5) has proven frustrating but was excellent in the G1 Epsom and looms large again, while HOOLIGAN TOMMY (12) is flying in easier grade and can surprise down in the weights.
